517
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:13,100
Come on. You're on.

518
00:28:13,100 --> 00:28:15,600
Please welcome the radiant

519
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:18,000
Susan Mayer!

520
00:28:26,700 --> 00:28:29,100
Tom, say something.

521
00:28:29,200 --> 00:28:31,900
A vision in white silk,

522
00:28:31,900 --> 00:28:33,900
chiffon with gold,

523
00:28:33,900 --> 00:28:35,600
hand-beaded french lace,

524
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:39,800
and lavender marabou.

525
00:28:41,600 --> 00:28:43,200
Susan Mayer.

526
00:28:46,900 --> 00:28:49,000
Oh, she's never looked better..

527
00:28:53,300 --> 00:28:56,700
Susan, I feel awful about what happened.

528
00:28:58,300 --> 00:29:00,100
Susan, talk to me.

529
00:29:01,800 --> 00:29:02,800
Okay, you want me to talk?

530
00:29:02,800 --> 00:29:05,500
You're going to find Helen Rowland,
and you're going to tell her the truth

531
00:29:05,500 --> 00:29:08,900
before everyone in this neighborhood thinks that
I'm the one sleeping with an underage boy.

532
00:29:08,900 --> 00:29:10,300
I can't do that.

533
00:29:10,300 --> 00:29:11,200
Why not?

534
00:29:11,200 --> 00:29:13,100
Because she'll tell Carlos, and he'll divorce me.

535
00:29:13,100 --> 00:29:16,200
So what? You obviously don't love him.

536
00:29:16,700 --> 00:29:18,800
I do love him. I-I do.

537
00:29:18,800 --> 00:29:22,000
It's just... complicated.

538
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:23,400
You know? There's --

539
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:26,000
there's got to be another way to fix this.

540
00:29:26,000 --> 00:29:29,000
God. You are so weak.

541
00:29:29,400 --> 00:29:31,200
Susan, don't be like this.

542
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:34,200
What did you expect, a hug?

543
00:29:42,500 --> 00:29:43,100
Hey.

544
00:29:43,100 --> 00:29:43,500
Shh.

545
00:29:43,500 --> 00:29:44,000
I took --

546
00:29:44,000 --> 00:29:45,500
Alexis is still here.

547
00:29:45,500 --> 00:29:46,600
Oh.

548
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:49,900
She was supposed to go to pilates,
but she got her period.

549
00:29:49,900 --> 00:29:50,800
You got to go.

550
00:29:50,800 --> 00:29:51,600
Just give me a second.

551
00:29:51,600 --> 00:29:53,700
No. She saw you at the park, okay?

552
00:29:53,700 --> 00:29:56,700
She knows what you're trying to do.
You're not the first person to approach me.

553
00:29:56,700 --> 00:29:58,100
Claire!

554
00:29:58,100 --> 00:29:59,900
How can you stay here after the way she treats you?

555
00:29:59,900 --> 00:30:01,700
She can be tough,

556
00:30:01,700 --> 00:30:03,300
but it comes with the territory, right?

557
00:30:03,300 --> 00:30:05,600
I would never treat you that way.

558
00:30:05,600 --> 00:30:08,300
Claire, what did you do with the aspirin?!

559
00:30:08,300 --> 00:30:11,900
I will give you a 20% bump on what
she's paying you, plus overtime.

560
00:30:11,900 --> 00:30:14,700
Damn it, Claire, where the hell are you?!

561
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:18,600
I don't take orders from your friends,

562
00:30:18,600 --> 00:30:21,700
I'm not a telephone answering service,
and I don't do laundry.

563
00:30:21,700 --> 00:30:22,600
Dishes?

564
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:24,400
Only the kids'.

565
00:30:24,500 --> 00:30:26,600
How fast can you pack?

566
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:34,300
I got a nanny

567
00:30:36,400 --> 00:30:37,800
Where are you going to go?

568
00:30:37,800 --> 00:30:38,800
I don't know,

569
00:30:38,800 --> 00:30:40,600
but I can't go home.

570
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:41,500
Are you afraid of your dad?

571
00:30:41,500 --> 00:30:44,300
No, it's not him, all right?

572
00:30:44,300 --> 00:30:47,200
It's -- it's me. My life is really messed up.

573
00:30:47,300 --> 00:30:48,400
It's bad.

574
00:30:48,400 --> 00:30:49,800
What's bad? You can tell me.

575
00:30:49,800 --> 00:30:51,600
No, I can't.

576
00:30:53,600 --> 00:30:55,800
It's better that you don't know.

577
00:31:04,200 --> 00:31:06,700
I already know a little.

578
00:31:29,200 --> 00:31:31,400
Hi, Danielle. How was school?

579
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:32,300
It was okay.

580
00:31:32,300 --> 00:31:35,600
Good. Where does Andrew keep his marijuana?

581
00:31:59,700 --> 00:32:04,400
Bree had resorted to extreme measures
to save her son's soul.

582
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:09,200
As she rummaged through Andrew's private possessions,

583
00:32:10,700 --> 00:32:15,800
it occurred to her that sometimes a little betrayal

584
00:32:15,800 --> 00:32:18,400
is good for the soul.

585
00:32:29,500 --> 00:32:31,900
I was really young, like 4.

586
00:32:31,900 --> 00:32:34,700
I heard my mom and my dad yelling.

587
00:32:34,700 --> 00:32:37,000
I heard them yell my name...

588
00:32:38,100 --> 00:32:39,600
and hers.

589
00:32:39,600 --> 00:32:41,300
Dana?

590
00:32:41,300 --> 00:32:43,000
Mm-hmm.

591
00:32:43,400 --> 00:32:45,300
So...

592
00:32:45,500 --> 00:32:49,100
I went down to the room, and I
saw them cleaning it up.

593
00:32:49,500 --> 00:32:51,600
Cleaning what up?

594
00:32:53,500 --> 00:32:55,300
Blood.

595
00:32:58,100 --> 00:33:00,300
Was it Dana's?

596
00:33:01,300 --> 00:33:03,300
I think so.

597
00:33:05,600 --> 00:33:09,500
I couldn't remember this for
the longest time, and then...

598
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:12,200
my mom killed herself,

599
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:15,300
and I started having these dreams.

600
00:33:16,300 --> 00:33:17,800
I-I don't even see Dana.

601
00:33:17,800 --> 00:33:20,800
I just -- I- I see --I see the blood

602
00:33:20,900 --> 00:33:23,400
and my mom picking me up

603
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:27,700
and putting --putting me on my bed
and whispering that it's not my fault.

604
00:33:29,100 --> 00:33:32,500
But after that, every time I'd
say her name, they'd get upset.

605
00:33:33,900 --> 00:33:36,600
I wasn't even allowed to say it anymore.

606
00:33:36,900 --> 00:33:40,100
I'm not sure I understand what you're saying.

607
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:43,800
I killed my baby sister.

608
00:33:46,500 --> 00:33:48,700
Zach, oh, my god.

609
00:33:48,800 --> 00:33:50,700
And they buried her

610
00:33:50,700 --> 00:33:52,600
to protect me.

611
00:34:24,200 --> 00:34:26,300
Helen. Do you have a minute?

612
00:34:26,300 --> 00:34:27,600
Oh, Gabrielle,

613
00:34:27,600 --> 00:34:31,400
I didn't get a chance to tell you how sorry I was
about what happened at the fundraiser.

614
00:34:31,400 --> 00:34:33,100
I didn't intend to cause a scene.

615
00:34:33,100 --> 00:34:35,600
No, it's okay. People didn't even notice.

616
00:34:35,700 --> 00:34:37,000
Well, this is a little awkward.

617
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:38,900
I-I know you're friends with Susan Mayer,

618
00:34:38,900 --> 00:34:41,800
but let's just say I had my reasons.

619
00:34:41,800 --> 00:34:43,700
It wasn't Susan.

620
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:47,100
It was me.

621
00:34:48,200 --> 00:34:48,900
What?

622
00:34:49,700 --> 00:34:53,300
I'm the one who was sleeping with your son.

623
00:34:56,300 --> 00:34:57,800
I'm so sorry.

624
00:34:59,900 --> 00:35:01,600
For how long?

625
00:35:02,200 --> 00:35:04,100
Almost a year.

626
00:35:04,500 --> 00:35:06,200
But it's over now.

627
00:35:07,600 --> 00:35:13,000
So when it started, he was...16?

628
00:35:14,100 --> 00:35:15,500
I think.

629
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:22,300
But, Helen, y-you have to
believe me -- it's over now.

630
00:35:22,300 --> 00:35:24,000
No, you're wrong.

631
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:26,800
It's not even close to being over.

632
00:35:34,400 --> 00:35:35,900
Hey, coach wants to see you.

633
00:35:35,900 --> 00:35:37,100
Really?

634
00:35:37,500 --> 00:35:39,700
Hey, I bet it's about my scholarship.

635
00:35:56,200 --> 00:35:57,600
Hello?

636
00:35:57,700 --> 00:35:59,900
Yes, this is she.

637
00:36:00,200 --> 00:36:04,400
Marijuana in his locker?
Oh, I'm just horrified.

638
00:36:04,400 --> 00:36:07,200
There must be some sort of terrible mistake.

639
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:11,400
Um, yeah, okay.
Well, I will be right down.

640
00:36:22,600 --> 00:36:27,900
Elsewhere, another, darker secret
was the object of an investigation.

641
00:36:27,900 --> 00:36:29,100
Mr. Linder.

642
00:36:29,900 --> 00:36:31,100
Mr. Linder!

643
00:36:31,100 --> 00:36:32,100
Huh?

644
00:36:32,500 --> 00:36:35,200
Detective Beckerman. This is detective Burnett.

645
00:36:35,200 --> 00:36:37,400
We were hoping for a minute of your time.

646
00:36:41,700 --> 00:36:45,200
If you know anything about Zach's
whereabouts, you need to tell me now.

647
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:45,900
Um...

648
00:36:45,900 --> 00:36:47,800
honey, what's going on?

649
00:36:48,200 --> 00:36:50,100
Zach's gone from Silvercrest.

650
00:36:50,100 --> 00:36:51,600
They found letters in his room --

651
00:36:51,600 --> 00:36:52,800
letters from julie.

652
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:54,700
Well, yes, they were writing to each other.

653
00:36:54,700 --> 00:36:56,800
I need to see those letters.

654
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:59,800
Mom, they're private.

655
00:36:59,800 --> 00:37:01,700
My son is missing.

656
00:37:03,400 --> 00:37:07,000
Julie, in the letters, did Zach
say anything about running away?

657
00:37:08,000 --> 00:37:09,500
No.

658
00:37:10,300 --> 00:37:11,900
There's your answer.

659
00:37:12,400 --> 00:37:12,900
Susan --

660
00:37:12,900 --> 00:37:15,900
if we hear anything, I will let you know right away.

661
00:37:15,900 --> 00:37:18,800
I understand how worried you must be.

662
00:37:19,500 --> 00:37:21,100
Obviously, you don't.

663
00:37:21,100 --> 00:37:24,200
Paul, my daughter doesn't lie.

664
00:37:34,100 --> 00:37:36,200
This was a very popular design.

665
00:37:36,200 --> 00:37:40,500
I must have sold several hundred of these
just like it about 10 years back.

666
00:37:40,500 --> 00:37:42,400
Do you keep any kind of documentation?

667
00:37:42,400 --> 00:37:46,500
Yeah, I have a list of customers' names
on file... somewhere.

668
00:37:46,500 --> 00:37:47,400
It's been a while.

669
00:37:47,400 --> 00:37:48,800
We'll need a copy of that list.

670
00:37:48,800 --> 00:37:50,200
Oh, sure.

671
00:37:50,400 --> 00:37:53,200
Wow, this chest looks like it's been through hell.

672
00:37:53,200 --> 00:37:55,000
Yeah, we pulled it out of Rockwater Lake.

673
00:37:55,000 --> 00:37:57,800
You could say by way of hell, considering.

674
00:37:58,600 --> 00:38:01,100
W-was there anything in the chest?

675
00:38:01,100 --> 00:38:03,300
It had a body inside --

676
00:38:03,300 --> 00:38:05,200
adult female.

677
00:38:06,300 --> 00:38:10,800
Yeah, but -- how do you fit a body
into a chest that size?

678
00:38:11,500 --> 00:38:14,400
It was chopped up.

679
00:38:41,700 --> 00:38:44,500
Of all the stupid, boneheaded decisions.

680
00:38:44,700 --> 00:38:46,300
What were you thinking?

681
00:38:46,300 --> 00:38:47,800
I was set up, all right?

682
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:49,400
The coach got an anonymous phone call.

683
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:52,000
Andrew, what does it matter? The pot was there.

684
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:54,500
I was holding it for a friend.

685
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:56,100
You know...

686
00:38:56,900 --> 00:39:00,100
I can't decide which is more humiliating --

687
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:03,200
the fact that my son got caught with pot in his locker

688
00:39:03,200 --> 00:39:06,900
or that he can't even come up with
a decent enough lie to explain it.

689
00:39:27,900 --> 00:39:30,200
Gabrielle believed there was an excellent chance

690
00:39:30,200 --> 00:39:35,300
Helen Rowland would inform Carlos of
his wife's extramarital activities.

691
00:39:37,400 --> 00:39:40,200
Gabrielle knew she had to come clean.

692
00:39:41,200 --> 00:39:41,900
Carlos?

693
00:39:41,900 --> 00:39:42,800
Yeah?

694
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:45,200
But coming clean...

695
00:39:46,800 --> 00:39:48,500
I, uh...

696
00:39:50,200 --> 00:39:53,300
was not one of Gabrielle's specialties.

697
00:39:53,300 --> 00:39:54,900
I'm going to bed.

698
00:39:55,100 --> 00:39:56,800
Thanks for the news flash.

699
00:40:13,300 --> 00:40:15,100
She turned me in.

700
00:40:18,200 --> 00:40:19,300
Carlos!

701
00:40:19,700 --> 00:40:22,500
Carlos, I'm so sorry. I am so sorry.

702
00:40:22,500 --> 00:40:23,100
Sorry for what?

703
00:40:23,100 --> 00:40:26,100
Just know that whatever happens,
I love you very, very much.

704
00:40:26,100 --> 00:40:27,800
FBI. Open the door.

705
00:40:29,400 --> 00:40:30,300
Oh, my god.

706
00:40:30,300 --> 00:40:32,600
FBI. If you do not open the door,

707
00:40:32,600 --> 00:40:35,800
I am authorized to enter the
premises by use of force.

708
00:40:40,500 --> 00:40:43,300
Carlos Solis, I have a warrant for your arrest.

709
00:40:43,300 --> 00:40:45,200
You have the right to remain silent.

710
00:40:45,200 --> 00:40:45,800
Huh?

711
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:48,700
Anything you say can and will be used
against you in a court of law.

712
00:40:48,700 --> 00:40:49,500
Call our lawyer.

713
00:40:49,500 --> 00:40:50,600
You have the right to speak with an attorney...

714
00:40:50,600 --> 00:40:52,300
- And have an attorney present during questioning.
- Carlos. what's happening?

715
00:40:52,300 --> 00:40:57,000
If you cannot afford a lawyer, one will be
appointed for you at government expense.

716
00:41:03,900 --> 00:41:05,500
Carlos, wait!

717
00:41:06,300 --> 00:41:09,200
Gabrielle, this will all be taken care of, I promise.

718
00:41:10,300 --> 00:41:12,000
I-I'm innocent, I swear to god.

719
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:14,000
It was Tanaka. He set me up.

720
00:41:26,200 --> 00:41:29,300
People are complicated creatures.

721
00:41:30,300 --> 00:41:34,800
On the one hand, able to perform
great acts of charity.

722
00:41:36,800 --> 00:41:38,200
On the other...

723
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:43,600
capable of the most underhanded
forms of betrayal.

724
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:49,700
It's a constant battle that rages within all of us

725
00:41:49,700 --> 00:41:53,000
between the better angels of our nature

726
00:41:53,800 --> 00:41:57,800
and the temptation of our inner demons.

727
00:42:01,300 --> 00:42:06,000
And sometimes, the only way
to ward off the darkness...

728
00:42:09,500 --> 00:42:12,800
is to shine the light of compassion.

729
00:42:21,800 --> 00:42:25,400
They took him away in handcuffs.

